        <div n="662-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-1"> Poor ladies! though their business be to play,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-2"> 'Tis hard they must be busy night and day:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-3"> Why should they want the privilege of men,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-4"> And take some small diversions now and then?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-5"> Had women been the makers of our laws;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-6"> (And why they were not, I can see no cause;)</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-7"> The men should slave at cards from morn to night;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-662-ROGP-line-8"> And female pleasures be to read and write.662-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
